Data Specification: City Sheet
1. Data Object Requirements
1.1 Core Principles
Source of Truth: All static content lives in /src/data/.

Format: Strict TypeScript Interfaces matching .json files.

Immutability: IDs and Slugs must not change once indexed by Google.

1.2 The City Object
File: /src/data/cities/[city-slug].json

Every city file must strictly follow this shape:

TypeScript

interface City {
  id: string;             // Unique UUID or stable string
  name: string;           // Display Name (e.g., "Paris")
  slug: string;           // URL-safe (e.g., "paris")
  country: string;        // Display (e.g., "France")
  hero_image: string;     // URL (curated)
  intro_vibe: string;     // 1 sentence summary
  
  // Quick Stats
  stats: {
    currency: string;     // "EUR (€)"
    plug_type: string;    // "Type C/E"
    best_time: string;    // "Apr-Jun, Sep-Nov"
  };

  // Logistics (Simple strings for list view)
  logistics: {
    safety: string[];     // Bullet points
    scams: string[];      // Specific warnings
    transit: string[];    // Tips
  };
  
  // The Lists
  must_eat: Place[];      // Array of places
  must_see: Place[];      // Array of places
}
1.3 The Place Object (Nested)
Used inside the must_eat and must_see arrays.

TypeScript

interface Place {
  id: string;             // Internal ID
  slug: string;           // URL-safe (e.g., "thipsamai-pad-thai")
  name_en: string;        // "Thipsamai Pad Thai"
  name_local: string;     // "ทิพย์สมัย ผัดไทยประตูผี" (CRITICAL FOR HOOK)
  category: "food" | "sight" | "activity"; 
  description: string;    // Max 280 chars
  image: string;          // Curated URL
  geo: {
    lat: number;
    lng: number;
    google_maps_id?: string; // Optional CID
  };
  tags: string[];         // For future filtering (e.g., "spicy", "historic")
}
2. URL & Slug Consistency
Rule: URLs are generated exclusively from the slug property.

Constraint:

City URL: /city/{city.slug}

Place URL: /city/{city.slug}/{place.slug}

Validation: The build script must throw an error if two items in the same city share a slug.

3. Data File Structure
The AI Builder must create this exact file tree:

Plaintext

/src
  /data
    /cities
      paris.json       <-- Contains full City object + nested Places
      bangkok.json
      tokyo.json
    taxonomy.ts        <-- Exports category definitions (colors, icons)
4. Taxonomy & Categories
File: /src/data/taxonomy.ts

Centralized definition for UI logic (colors/icons) based on category.

TypeScript

export const CATEGORIES = {
  food: {
    label: "Must Eat",
    icon: "Utensils",     // Lucide name
    color: "amber"        // Tailwind color key
  },
  sight: {
    label: "Must See",
    icon: "Camera",
    color: "indigo"
  },
  activity: {
    label: "Experience",
    icon: "Ticket",
    color: "emerald"
  }
}
